0. Init mysqld
$ scripts/mysql_install_db

1. Run mysqld with the hot backup library (should exist in the lib directory)
$ LD_PRELOAD=PATH_TO_WHERE_HOT_BACKUP_LIVES/libHotBackup.so ./mysqld_safe

2. Install the backup plugin (should exist in the lib/mysql/plugin directory)
mysql> install plugin tokubackup soname 'tokubackup.so';

3. Check out the backup variables
mysql> show variables like 'tokubackup%';

4. Backup to /tmp/backup1047 directory.  This blocks until the backup is complete.
mysql> set tokubackup_dir="/tmp/backup1047";

5. Check if the backup worked
msyql> select @@tokubackup_last_error;

6. Work to do
a. Support multiple directories
b. Add status variables
c. Implement the error callback
d. Add tokubackup_last_error_str variable
e. Hack mysqld_safe to auto preload the hot backup lib if it finds one
